@startuml ticket-lifecycle-sla-side-effects
title Ticket Solve, Close, Reopen, and SLA Lifecycle Side Effects
hide footbox
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontSize 16
skinparam sequence {
  ArrowColor #111111
  LifeLineBorderColor #111111
  LifeLineBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ParticipantBorderColor #111111
  ParticipantBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  ActorBorderColor #111111
  ActorBackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  GroupBorderColor #111111
  GroupBackgroundColor #EEEEEE
}

actor "Agent" as Agent
participant "Ticket UI" as UI
participant "Routes +\nValidation" as Routes
participant "Auth + Workspace\nGuards" as Guards
participant "Ticket\nController" as Controller
participant "Ticket\nService" as TicketService
participant "Ticket + Conversation\nModels" as TicketModels
participant "SLA Runtime\nService" as SlaRuntime
participant "Live Event\nService" as Events

== 1. Submit lifecycle action ==
Agent -> UI: Solve, close, reopen,\nor set status
UI -> Routes: POST /api/tickets/:id/solve\nPOST /api/tickets/:id/close\nPOST /api/tickets/:id/reopen\nPOST /api/tickets/:id/status
Routes -> Guards: auth, active user/member,\nowner/admin/agent role
Routes -> Routes: validate id and status body
Routes -> Controller: lifecycle controller
Controller -> TicketService: solveTicket, closeTicket,\nreopenTicket, or updateTicketStatus

== 2. Authorize and validate transition ==
TicketService -> TicketModels: load ticket in active workspace
TicketService -> TicketService: enforce explicit transition rules

== 3. Apply status change ==
alt solve or close path
  TicketService -> SlaRuntime: solve/status solved marks\nresolution SLA at event time
  TicketService -> TicketModels: status = solved or closed;\nclosedAt only for closed
else reopen path
  TicketService -> SlaRuntime: clear resolvedAt and resume\nremaining resolution time
  TicketService -> TicketModels: status = open;\nclosedAt cleared by model
end

== 4. Apply SLA side effects ==
SlaRuntime -> SlaRuntime: pause/resume/resolve resolution SLA\nbased on next status
SlaRuntime --> TicketService: updated stored SLA fields
TicketService -> TicketModels: save ticket status and SLA

== 5. Publish lifecycle event ==
TicketService -> Events: publish ticket.status_changed,\nticket.solved, ticket.closed,\nor ticket.reopened
Events -> Events: update internal rooms and\nwidget conversation when linked
TicketService --> Controller: compact lifecycle response
Controller --> UI: success.ticket.statusUpdated,\nsolved, closed, or reopened
UI --> Agent: Show lifecycle state

@enduml
